In the first task you downloaded a video from YouTube (yt-dlp - utility in Linux) and chopped it into 
frames of images using ffmpeg. Now, you should repeat the process once again, generating some 30 frames
per second on a 1 minute continuous portion of the video (30x60 = 1800 images) creating around 1800 images.
These 1800 images are to be re-converted into a video of 1 minute duration at frame rate of 30 (ffmpeg can be used here too).
Upload the video and share the link to the video you created from images. 


ffmpeg commands
1)to get 1800 slides
=>ffmpeg -ss 00:00:00 -t 60 -i test.mp4 -vf fps=30 frames_%04d.png

2)to get a 1min video
=>ffmpeg -framerate 30 -i frames_%04d.png -c:v libx264 -pix_fmt yuv420p output.mp4
